## PHASE 0 CLOSED — all 9 acceptance criteria met

Slice 9 (Playwright E2E + CI integration) merged. Both CI jobs
(ci + e2e) green and required on main.

Phase 0 took 6 working days: scaffold → RLS multi-tenancy → auth →
onboarding → invitations → observability → CI → E2E.

What exists now:
- Multi-tenant SaaS with database-enforced isolation (Postgres RLS +
  FORCE RLS, withTenant helper, 4 SECURITY DEFINER functions)
- Bearer-token auth (argon2, SHA-256 session hashing)
- Full owner onboarding (5 steps) + admin invitation flow
- Sentry + PostHog wiring (no-DSN-no-op contract)
- 117 backend tests + 1 Playwright E2E, all green in CI
- CI on every PR: lint + typecheck + test + build + e2e, branch
  protected

Bugs surfaced by E2E, logged for pre-pilot fix:
- Zod .optional() ordering bug in branding + invite forms (empty
  strings rejected before .optional() rescues) — onboarding funnel
  leak, fix before pilot demo

Carried forward (deferred.md highlights):
- Windows Turbo crash (hidden bugs in slices 6, 7, 8b — now the
  highest-leverage post-Phase-0 fix)
- @types/react override removal when DefinitelyTyped fixes upstream
- dotenv-cli test wrapper → shared test bootstrap
- HttpOnly cookie session migration
- Sentry/PostHog dashboard verification once accounts set up

The "tests pass, runtime fails" pattern hit 9 times across Phase 0.
Lesson banked permanently: every toolchain layer has its own
resolution model; manual/CI verification before "done" is
non-negotiable.

